# React SuperAdmin Project Rules

## Project Structure

This is a monorepo with pnpm workspaces containing:

- `packages/core`: Core framework with TypeScript, React hooks, contexts, and utilities
- `packages/web`: Web admin interface using Vite, React, Tailwind CSS

## Development Commands

- Use `pnpm dev` to start development (runs web package)
- Use `pnpm build` to build both packages
- Use `pnpm build:core` or `pnpm build:web` for individual packages

## Key Patterns

- Components use PascalCase naming (e.g., DataTable, ResourceForm)
- Hooks use camelCase with 'use' prefix (e.g., useAuth, useFilters)
- Core package exports reusable framework code
- Web package imports from core and provides admin interface
- Both packages use TypeScript with strict mode

## File Organization

- Core package: components/, contexts/, hooks/, types/, utils/
- Web package: components/crud/, components/forms/, components/layout/, components/ui/
- Use relative imports within packages, package imports between packages

## Technology Stack

- React 18+ with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Vite for web package build tool
- pnpm as package manager with workspace support

## PM Workflow - GitHub Project Management

- **Project ID**: Always use `2` (Web Components project)
- **Owner**: Always use `batmaster`
- **Commands**:
  - List project items: `gh project item-list 2 --owner batmaster --format json`
  - Add items to project: `gh project item-add 2 --owner batmaster --url <issue-url>`
  - Edit item status: `gh project item-edit --project-id PVT_kwHOAC25es4BA-UG --id <item-id> --field-id <field-id> --value <status>`
  - View project: `gh project view 2 --owner batmaster --format json`
  - List fields: `gh project field-list 2 --owner batmaster --format json`
- **Never ask for owner or project selection** - always specify them explicitly
- **3-Phase Approach**: Every component needs Code Implementation, Testing (90%+ coverage), Documentation (MDX + JSDoc)
- **Status Management**: Move null/empty status items to "Todo" immediately
- **Continuous Work**: Keep reviewing React Admin docs and built docs for new component needs
